According to one of the world's leading
experts on data validation Edward Craft,

6
00:00:14.630 --> 00:00:16.780
a data graph should show the data and

7
00:00:16.780 --> 00:00:19.430
induce the viewer to think
about the substance.

8
00:00:19.430 --> 00:00:23.680
In order to achieve this,
he introduced the concept of data ink.

9
00:00:23.680 --> 00:00:28.034
The idea is that a large share of ink
on a graph should present the data.

10
00:00:28.034 --> 00:00:31.186
The share of Data-Ink is compared
in Ratio which is defined as

11
00:00:31.186 --> 00:00:34.960
the Data-Ink divided by total
ink used to print the graph.

